=There are two standard methods to create a new file in java, either directly with the help of file class
or indirectly with the help of FileOutputStream class by creating an object of both files in both approaches

METHODS TO CREATE FILES IN JAVA
1)Using the File class
2)Using the FileOutputStream class

=Both classes provide some methods that are mainly used for operations regarding files i.e
create files
write files
compare two path names
check whether a specific file is present
NOTE: To specify a directory is different in various operating systems; i.e
In Linux and Mac
=/Users/Folder/
In Windows: '\\' is used instead of '/' to escape '\' character
=\\Users\\Folder\\